loud.name: 2002 Rainsong Carbon Fiber guitar
loud.description: Fabulous, rare Rainsong 38 inch dreadnaught steel string acoustic electric guitar in excellent condition except for small nick that does not affect its amazing sound which is loud and clear. Strung with Elixer strings. This is a high end instrument that is just the right size for most anyone.  It has Fischer electronics and includes a quality gig bag and strap. You will not be disappointed. Best offer accepted!

loud.description: Extremely rare Epiphone Blackstone from 1933!!!Replacement tuners ( period accurate)Comes with soft casePlays nice with low action Smallish archtop , very comfortable to play on your lap.New strings and intonation ( 13-56)Pretty loud for a small archtop No cracks or repairs ( that I know off )Want a small 1930’s Epiphone Archtop ?This may be it !In ConcordJeff

famous.name: Famous FS-1 Soprano Ukulele OBO
famous.description: Pretty little soprano, nice build with super-thin mahogany laminate, but with a sound that will rival most solid-wood ukes. Extremely light, with excellent projection and beautiful resonance. The Famous FS-1 is a Japanese build, identical to the Kiwaya KS-1, but sold only to the Japanese market. This older uke has a Rosewood fingerboard, which you won't find in production any longer...the newer ones are walnut.  Subtle striping at the soundhole is nice touch. Low action and great intonation, it's got a classic ukulele sound. Friction tuners. Tiny scratch on the headstock, mark on the first fret - see the photos for detail.Reasonable offers are welcome.

famous.name: SUPRO Blues King 8
famous.description: Nearly new Supro in pristine condition seeks a new home with a guitar lover. This is an amp to LOVE, for its complete integrity as a well-built, cool design that makes your guitar sing as a superb sounding instrument that makes playing a true pleasure, to treasure!Versatile 1-watt Tube AmplifierHailing from Chicago's rock 'n' roll scene, the Supro Blues King 1x8 tube combo amplifier delivers classic tones and styling suitable for the modern guitarist. This 1-watt amp is perfect for the bedroom guitarist since it produces all the crunch and attitude of early Supro amps without all the unwanted volume. The Blues King has a Class A power section, a custom-designed eight-inch Supro speaker, and simplified controls to provide you with perfect tones right out of the box. You'll be able to fatten up your tone with the footswitchable boost that works especially well with single-coil guitars. Want an amp that's descended from the classics? Choose the Supro Blues King 8.Custom-designed speakerAnother thing that sets the Blues King 8 apart is its custom-made 8 speaker. This speaker is designed to capture the essence of the original speakers that made Supro famous. This speaker has a bold midrange that breaks up perfectly as you increase the volume. And guitarists here at Sweetwater enjoy the line output that eliminates the need to mic your amp for recording.Supro Blues King 8 Tube Combo Amplifier Features:Master volume control to create huge, saturated tones at low volumeCustom BK8 speaker produces extra punchLine output eliminates the need to mic your amp for recordingBoost strengthens midrange responseClass A power section delivers classic Supro tonesOptional footswitch engages boost (sold separately)

famous.name: Double Track Reverb
famous.description: Keeley 30ms Automatic Double Tracker Features:Double Tracking Effect Slap Back ReverbStudio Two Chamber ReverbTrue Stereo ChorusThe stereo effect pedal offers an array of studio style doubling effects used for creating thicker, fuller sounding instruments.  Also included in the effect pedal is a reverb that simulates the famous chamber in Studio Two. The Keeley 30ms is designed to work with guitar, bass, keyboard, even vocals“Since the early days of automatic double tracking pioneered by Ken Townsend and John Lennon at Abbey Road Studios, this technique has become the de facto way of creating recordings that sound bigger and fuller by making it sound like two guitars, or singers, or instrumentalists are playing at same time,” said chief engineer Robert Keeley. “The Keeley 30ms Automatic Double Tracker offers musicians the ability to take these techniques with them out on the road with a wide range of tools needed for crafting unique double tracking schemes.”The Keeley Engineering 30ms Automatic Double Tracker pedal can be used in mono with a built in “Abbey Verb” reverb control, or in stereo as the Double Tracker Pro. The 30ms offers altered and detuned effects like a chorus pedal might sound, only without the regularity of a LFO oscillator in Dimension Mode. In this mode you have the ability to create up to two different voices for a stereo double tracked field. The user controls the tuning and delay for results that are stunning mono or through two amplifiers in stereo. Abbey Mode offers something more similar to a conventional chorus in that it simulates synched tape decks running in parallel with varying tape speeds. Stereo or mono this mode gives players a wide, lush sound without sounding like a conventional chorus pedal. Lastly the team at Keeley created a unique Slapback Mode for rockabilly sounds. The Slapback is now a double tracked echo with the two altered voices. Add the Keeley Abbey Verb to this mode to create really new effects.In Stereo Double Tracker Pro mode the unit drops the reverb channel in favor of complete control over the double tracked voices. Each of the two voices can be tuned up to 30 cents sharp and flat. Those voices are then delayed by up to 30 milliseconds for subtle to very distinctive doubling sounds. The user can program by internal switches the wet output to have either dry and effected sounds, or just the effect, giving them true double tracking in stereo, live.
